<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Data on Seattle Urbanism Guide</title><link>https://seattle.urbanism-guide.com/pr-preview/28/data/</link><description>Recent content in Data on Seattle Urbanism Guide</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en-us</language><atom:link href="https://seattle.urbanism-guide.com/pr-preview/28/data/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Pedestrian Collision Analysis</title><link>https://seattle.urbanism-guide.com/pr-preview/28/data/ped-collisions/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://seattle.urbanism-guide.com/pr-preview/28/data/ped-collisions/</guid><description>&lt;h1 id="pedestrian-collision-analysis">Pedestrian Collision Analysis&lt;a class="anchor" href="#pedestrian-collision-analysis">#&lt;/a>&lt;/h1>
&lt;p>Interactive charts built from &lt;a href="https://data-seattlecitygis.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/SeattleCityGIS::sdot-collisions-all-years">SDOT&amp;rsquo;s collision dataset&lt;/a>, filtered to pedestrian-involved incidents (&lt;code>PEDCOUNT &amp;gt;= 1&lt;/code>). Data is fetched live from Seattle&amp;rsquo;s ArcGIS open data API each time you load this page.&lt;/p>
&lt;p>See also: &lt;a href="https://seattle.urbanism-guide.com/pr-preview/28/guides/pedestrian/">Pedestrian Safety &amp;amp; Infrastructure guide&lt;/a> | &lt;a href="https://seattle.urbanism-guide.com/pr-preview/28/data/">Data Dashboards&lt;/a>&lt;/p>

&lt;div id="ped-analysis">

 
